  "title": "Junior Scientist (Discovery Chemistry), EDDC",
  "description": "<p>The Experimental Drug Development Centre (EDDC) is a national platform in Singapore dedicated to the discovery and development of novel therapeutics through collaboration with the public sector and industry partners. EDDC is seeking a highly motivated Junior Scientist to join the Discovery Chemistry (Medicinal Chemistry) team. The successful candidate will be responsible for the design, synthesis and characterisation of small organic molecules to support interdisciplinary drug discovery projects. The role offers an exciting opportunity to be part of a dynamic team working to advance innovative drug discovery research.<br /><br /><strong>Key Roles and Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Plan and carry out the synthesis of small organic molecules, including synthetic route design, reaction condition optimisation, and purification and characterisation of products \n</li><li>Analyse experimental results and present findings to the project team \n</li><li>Maintain accurate experimental records in electronic lab notebook \n</li><li>Support routine laboratory operations, including equipment maintenance, lab safety compliance and general \nhousekeeping </li></ul><p><strong>Job Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>BSc in Chemistry or a Chemistry related field \n</li><li>Strong foundation in organic and/or medicinal chemistry \n</li><li>Experience in organic synthesis, chromatographic purification methods and analytical techniques such as NMR, LCMS and HPLC is required <br /></li><li>Attention to detail, strong analytical and problem-solving skills \n</li><li>Self-motivated, excellent organisational, communication and interpersonal skills</li></ul>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 2,
